@attribute [Route("/components/" + nameof(HxCollapse))]
@attribute [Route("/components/" + nameof(HxCollapseToggleButton))]
@attribute [Route("/components/" + nameof(HxCollapseToggleElement))]

<ApiDoc Type="typeof(HxCollapse)">

    <DocHeading Title="Basic usage" />
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxCollapse_Demo_Basic)" Tabs="false" />

    <DocHeading Title="Horizontal" />
	<p>You can change the animation direction using the <code>CollapseDirection</code> parameter.</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxCollapse_Demo_Horizontal)" />

    <DocHeading Title="Multiple targets" />
	<p>You can use the <code>CollapseTarget</code> selector to toggle multiple targets.</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxCollapse_Demo_MultipleTargets)" />

    <DocHeading Title="Custom toggle element" />
	<p>Use <code>HxCollapseToggleElement</code> (<code>with ElementName="..."</code>) instead of <code>HxCollapseToggleButton</code> to create a custom toggler (usually you will add <code>role="button"</code> to apply a pointer cursor type).</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxCollapse_Demo_CustomToggleElement)" />

    <DocHeading Title="Start as expanded" Id="InitiallyExpanded" />
	<p>The <code>HxCollapse</code> starts in a collapsed state by default. If you want it to be expanded, set the <code>InitiallyExpanded</code> parameter:</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxCollapse_Demo_InitiallyExpanded)" />

    <DocHeading Title="Programming" />
    <p>You can use the <code>ShowAsync()</code> and <code>HideAsync()</code> methods to expand/collapse the component from your code.</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxCollapse_Demo_Programming)" />

    <DocHeading Title="Accessibility" />
	<p>
		<code>HxCollapseToggleButton</code> and <code>HxCollapseToggleElement</code> automatically render <code>data-bs-toggle="collapse"</code>,
		<code>aria-expanded</code>, and (when <code>CollapseTarget</code> is an ID selector, e.g. <code>#myCollapse</code>) <code>aria-controls</code>, so assistive technologies are informed
		of the expanded/collapsed state and the region being controlled. Make sure the controlled <code>HxCollapse</code> has an <code>Id</code> that matches the toggle's target.
	</p>

</ApiDoc>

